==English==
===Etymology===
From mediæval Latin [[morphea]], from Italian [[morfea]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μόρφα]]''' 
(''morfa'') "shape, [[form]], build"

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mɔ:fju:/

===Noun===
'''morphew'''
# a [[blemish]] or [[mark]] on the skin
#:*'''1985''': ‘Even the pox is afraid to touch thy '''morphewed''' carcase.’ — John Fowles, ''A Maggot''